    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1987 developer Stan Olsen turned the historic 1930s ranch and former limestone quarry into a premier golf destination.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://grokipedia.com/page/black_diamond_florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The community sits on 1,320 acres of sand hills that inspired Olsen’s vision for a private golf club.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.blackdiamondranch.com/our-story/history"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Black Diamond lies just north of Citrus County’s geographic center and borders Pine Ridge to the north and Lecanto to the south.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
